  "name": "debugtools-map-hub-modern-release",
  "description": "Release counterpart of debugtools-map-hub-modern-debug.json (Issue #11 slice 2). Replays debugtools-hub-modern-release.json's own already-verified 259-frame input script verbatim (proving, as that scenario documents, that FE8_EXPANSION_DEBUGTOOLS_ENABLED being compiled out means the title-screen SELECT+R hotkey never diverts Title_IDLE's vanilla A/START handling, so this modern release build's deterministic outcome for that input script is a stable, unchanging frame -- expected_framebuffer_hash fnv1a64-rgb24:d11078d0ec60076d matches debugtools-hub-modern-release.json's own 'chapter2-interactive-stable'/'post-interactive-cursor-response' checkpoints exactly, frame for frame, byte for byte), then appends this slice's new map-hotkey tail: two FE8_EXPANSION_DEBUGTOOLS_MAP_HOTKEY_MASK (SELECT+L) pulses, followed by the same DOWN/A/RIGHT/RIGHT/B/DOWN/A/RIGHT/B/B tap sequence used in the debug-build map-hub scenario. In this release build, DebugTools_MapHotkeyCheck (src/debugtools_registry.c) compiles to an empty no-op body and DebugTools_IsHubActive() always returns 0, so src/playerphase.c's PlayerPhase_MainIdle never returns early for these keys and gDebugToolsProbe is never written by any debugtools code path -- there is no live sHubActive symbol at all in this build (see docs/debugtools.md). Every appended checkpoint's framebuffer_hash is proven identical to the pre-existing frozen frame and to every other checkpoint in this scenario: the map hotkey (like the title hotkey before it) has zero observable effect, and gDebugToolsProbe.hubOpenCount/registeredActionCount/lastRegisterResult/launcherArmed all stay 0x00000000 throughout, exactly like debugtools-hub-modern-release.json's own probes -- proving the map-phase debug entry point is compiled out, not merely unreached, and introduces no new behavior whatsoever into a release build.",
